# 🧑‍💻 PSA Real-Time Scenario

## Incident

A user reports:

> I tried to make a payment at 10:30 AM, but the payment failed.

A reasonable investigation flow might be:

### Step 1: Go to the log directory

```bash
cd /app/logs
```

### Step 2: Find recently modified files

```bash
ls -ltr
```

### Step 3: Check recent log lines

```bash
tail -n 200 payment.log
```

### Step 4: Search for errors

```bash
tail -n 500 payment.log | grep -i "error"
```

### Step 5: Search by transaction ID if available

```bash
grep "TXN12345" payment.log
```

### Step 6: Inspect the complete surrounding context

```bash
less payment.log
```

Inside `less`:

```text
/TXN12345
```

The main lesson is this:

```text
Do not search only for the word ERROR.

Better investigation keys can include:

Timestamp
Transaction ID
Request ID
User ID
Order ID
Correlation ID
Error code
Service name
```

In production support, a generic `grep ERROR` may return thousands of unrelated failures. Good troubleshooting narrows the search to the specific incident.

